obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (7633)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7633&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Investigation`
  line `Agency Act, 2008.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India and it applies also--`
  line
  line `(a) to citizens of India outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) to persons in the service of the Government wherever they may be; ^1***`
  line
  line `(c) to persons on ships and aircrafts registered in India wherever they may be ^2[and].`
  line
  line `^2[(d) to persons who commit a Scheduled Offence beyond India against the Indian citizens or`
  line `affecting the interest of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by Act 16 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (7634)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "a Special Court Constituted" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7634&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Agency" means the National Investigation Agency constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(c) "High Court" means the High Court within whose jurisdiction the Special Court is situated;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules;`
  line
  line `(e) "Public Prosecutor" means a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public Prosecutor or a Special`
  line `Public Prosecutor appointed under section 15;`
  line
  line `(f) "Schedule" means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "Scheduled Offence" means an offence specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(h) "Special Court" means ^1[a Court of Session designated as Special Court] under section 11 or,`
  line `as the case may be, under section 22;`
  line
  line `(i) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Code shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any enactment or any provision thereof shall, in relation to an area in`
  line `which such enactment or such provision is not in force, be construed as a reference to the corresponding`
  line `law or the relevant provision of the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (7635)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of National Investigation Agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2019, s. 4 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7635&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the Police Act,`
  line `1861 (5 of 1861), the Central Government may constitute a special agency to be called the National`
  line `Investigation Agency for investigation and prosecution of offences under the Acts specified in the`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any orders which the Central Government may make in this behalf, officers of the`
  line `Agency shall have throughout India ^1[and, subject to any international treaty or domestic law of the`
  line `concerned country, outside India] in relation to the investigation of Scheduled Offences and arrest of`
  line `persons concerned in such offences, all the powers, duties, privileges and liabilities which police officers`
  line `have in connection with the investigation of offences committed therein.`
  line
  line `(3) Any officer of the Agency of, or above, the rank of Sub-Inspector may, subject to any orders`
  line `which the Central Government may make in this behalf, exercise throughout India, any of the powers of`
  line `the officer-in-charge of a police station in the area in which he is present for the time being and when so`
  line `exercising such powers shall, subject to any such orders as aforesaid, be deemed to be an officer-incharge of a police station discharging the functions of such an officer within the limits of his station.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (7636)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Superintendence of National Investigation Agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7636&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The superintendence of the Agency`
  line `shall vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The administration of the Agency shall vest in an officer designated as the Director-General`
  line `appointed in this behalf by the Central Government who shall exercise in respect of the Agency such of`
  line `the powers exercisable by a Director-General of Police in respect of the police force in a State, as the`
  line `Central Government may specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (7637)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Manner of constitution of Agency and conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7637&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Agency shall be constituted in such manner as may be prescribed and the`
  line `conditions of service of persons employed in the Agency shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (7638)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Investigation of Scheduled Offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 2019, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7638&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of information and recording thereof under`
  line `section 154 of the Code relating to any Scheduled Offence the officer-in-charge of the police station shall`
  line `forward the report to the State Government forthwith.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the report under sub-section (1), the State Government shall forward the report to`
  line `the Central Government as expeditiously as possible.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of report from the State Government, the Central Government shall determine on the`
  line `basis of information made available by the State Government or received from other sources, within`
  line `fifteen days from the date of receipt of the report, whether the offence is a Scheduled Offence or not and`
  line `also whether, having regard to the gravity of the offence and other relevant factors, it is a fit case to be`
  line `investigated by the Agency.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Central Government is of the opinion that the offence is a Scheduled Offence and it is a`
  line `fit case to be investigated by the Agency, it shall direct the Agency to investigate the said offence.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if the Central Government is of the opinion`
  line `that a Scheduled Offence has been committed which is required to be investigated under this Act, it may,`
  line `suo motu, direct the Agency to investigate the said offence.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any direction has been given under sub-section (4) or sub-section (5), the State`
  line `Government and any police officer of the State Government investigating the offence shall not proceed`
  line `with the investigation and shall forthwith transmit the relevant documents and records to the Agency.`
  line
  line `(7) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that till the Agency takes up the investigation of`
  line `the case, it shall be the duty of the officer-in-charge of the police station to continue the investigation.`
  line
  line `^1[(8) Where the Central Government is of the opinion that a Scheduled Offence has been committed`
  line `at any place outside India to which this act extends, it may direct the Agency to register the case and take`
  line `up investigation as if such offence has been committed in India.br`
  line
  line `(9) For the purposes of sub-section (8), the Special Court at New Delhi shall have the jurisdiction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (7639)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to transfer investigation to State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7639&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `While investigating any offence under`
  line `this Act, the Agency, having regard to the gravity of the offence and other relevant factors, may—`
  line
  line `(a) if it is expedient to do so, request the State Government to associate itself with the`
  line `investigation; or`
  line
  line `(b) with the previous approval of the Central Government, transfer the case to the State`
  line `Government for investigation and trial of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (7640)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to investigate connected offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7640&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `While investigating any Scheduled Offence, the`
  line `Agency may also investigate any other offence which the accused is alleged to have committed if the`
  line `offence is connected with the Scheduled Offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (7641)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `State Government to extend assistance to National Investigation Agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7641&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The State`
  line `Government shall extend all assistance and co-operation to the Agency for investigation of the Scheduled`
  line Offences.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (7642)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of State Government to investigate Scheduled Offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7642&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided`
  line `in this Act, nothing contained in this Act shall affect the powers of the State Government to investigate`
  line `and prosecute any Scheduled Offence or other offences under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (7643)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of Central Government to designate Court of Session as Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7643&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `11. Power of Central Government to ^1[designate Court of Session as] Special Courts.-- (1) ^2[The`
  line `Central Government shall, in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, for the trial of Scheduled Offences, designate one or more Courts of Session as Special`
  line `Court] for such area or areas, or for such case or class or group of cases, as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `^3[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "High Court" means the High`
  line `Court of the State in which a Court of Session to be designated as Special Court is functioning.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where any question arises as to the jurisdiction of any Special Court, it shall be referred to the`
  line `Central Government whose decision in the matter shall be final.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(8) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby provided that the attainment, ^5[by the Sessions Judge of`
  line `the Court of Session referred to in sub-section (1)], of the age of superannuation under the rules`
  line `applicable to him in the service to which he belongs shall not affect his continuance as ^6[ judge of the`
  line `Special Court and the appointing authority in consultation with the Central Government] may by order`
  line `direct that he shall continue as judge until a specified date or until completion of the trial of the case or`
  line `cases before him ^7[,whichever is earlier].`
  line
  line `^8[(9) When more than one Special Court is designated for an area or areas, the senior-most Judge shall`
  line `distribute the business among them.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "constitute" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, for the trial of Scheduled`
  line `Offences, constitute one or more Special Courts" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line `4. Sub-section (3), (4), (5), (6) and (7) omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "by a person appointed as a Judge or an additional Judge of a Special Court" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "such judge or additional judge and the Central Government" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "as may be specified in that order" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 16 of 2019, s. 6, for sub-section (9) (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (7644)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Place of sitting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7644&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A Special Court may, on its own motion, or on an application made by the`
  line `Public Prosecutor and if it considers it expedient or desirable so to do, sit for any of its proceedings at any`
  line `place other than its ordinary place of sitting.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (7645)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Jurisdiction of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7645&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, every`
  line `Scheduled Offence investigated by the Agency shall be tried only by the Special Court within whose local`
  line `jurisdiction it was committed.`
  line
  line `(2) If, having regard to the exigencies of the situation prevailing in a State if,—`
  line
  line `(a) it is not possible to have a fair, impartial or speedy trial; or`
  line
  line `(b) it is not feasible to have the trial without occasioning the breach of peace or grave risk to the`
  line `safety of the accused, the witnesses, the Public Prosecutor or a judge of the Special Court or any of`
  line `them; or`
  line
  line `(c) it is not otherwise in the interests of justice,`
  line
  line `the Supreme Court may transfer any case pending before a Special Court to any other Special Court`
  line `within that State or in any other State and the High Court may transfer any case pending before a Special`
  line `Court situated in that State to any other Special Court within the State.`
  line
  line `(3) The Supreme Court or the High Court, as the case may be, may act under this section either on the`
  line `application of the Central Government or a party interested and any such application shall be made by`
  line `motion, which shall, except when the applicant is the Attorney-General for India, be supported by an`
  line `affidavit or affirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (7646)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Powers of Special Courts with respect to other offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7646&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) When trying any offence, a`
  line `Special Court may also try any other offence with which the accused may, under the Code be charged, at`
  line `the same trial if the offence is connected with such other offence.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in the course of any trial under this Act of any offence, it is found that the accused person has`
  line `committed any other offence under this Act or under any other law, the Special Court may convict such`
  line `person of such other offence and pass any sentence or award punishment authorised by this Act or, as the`
  line `case may be, under such other law`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (7647)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Public Prosecutors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7647&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint a person to be the Public`
  line `Prosecutor and may appoint one or more persons to be the Additional Public Prosecutor or Additional`
  line `Public Prosecutors:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may also appoint for any case or class or group of cases a`
  line `Special Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public`
  line `Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor under this section unless he has been in practice as an Advocate`
  line `for not less than seven years or has held any post, for a period of not less than seven years, under the`
  line `Union or a State, requiring special knowledge of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person appointed as a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public Prosecutor or a Special`
  line `Public Prosecutor under this section shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of`
  line `clause (u) of section 2 of the Code, and the provisions of the Code shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (7648)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Procedure and powers of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7648&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Special Court may take cognizance of any`
  line `offence, without the accused being committed to it for trial, upon receiving a complaint of facts that`
  line `constitute such offence or upon a police report of such facts.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence triable by a Special Court is punishable with imprisonment for a term not`
  line `exceeding three years or with fine or with both, the Special Court may, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sub-section (1) of section 260 or section 262 of the Code, try the offence in a summary way`
  line `in accordance with the procedure prescribed in the Code and the provisions of sections 263 to 265 of the`
  line `Code shall, so far as may be, apply to such trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that when, in the course of a summary trial under this sub-section, it appears to the Special`
  line `Court that the nature of the case is such that it is not desirable to try it in a summary way, the Special`
  line `Court shall recall any witnesses who may have been examined and proceed to re-hear the case in the`
  line `manner provided by the provisions of the Code for the trial of such offence and the said provisions shall`
  line `apply to, and in relation to, a Special Court as they apply to and in relation to a Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial under this section, it shall be`
  line `lawful for a Special Court to pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year and with`
  line `fine which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, a Special Court shall, for the purpose of trial of any`
  line `offence, have all the powers of a Court of Session and shall try such offence as if it were a Court of`
  line `Session so far as may be in accordance with the procedure prescribed in the Code for the trial before a`
  line `Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, every case transferred to a Special Court under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13 shall be dealt with as if such case had been transferred under section 406 of`
  line `the Code to such Special Court.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, but subject to the provisions of section 299 of`
  line `the Code, a Special Court may, if it thinks fit and for reasons to be recorded by it, proceed with the trial in`
  line `the absence of the accused or his pleader and record the evidence of any witness, subject to the right of`
  line `the accused to recall the witness for cross-examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (7649)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Protection of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7649&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, the proceedings`
  line `under this Act may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, be held in camera if the Special Court so`
  line desires.
  line
  line `(2) On an application made by a witness in any proceeding before it or by the Public Prosecutor in`
  line `relation to such witness or on its own motion, if the Special Court is satisfied that the life of such witness`
  line `is in danger, it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, take such measures as it deems fit for keeping`
  line `the identity and address of such witness secret.`
  line
  line `(3) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (2), the`
  line `measures which a Special Court may take under that sub-section may include—`
  line
  line `(a) the holding of the proceedings at a place to be decided by the Special Court;`
  line
  line `(b) the avoiding of the mention of the names and addresses of the witnesses in its orders or`
  line `judgments or in any records of the case accessible to public;`
  line
  line `(c) the issuing of any directions for securing that the identity and address of the witnesses are not`
  line `disclosed; and`
  line
  line `(d) a decision that it is in the public interest to order that all or any of the proceedings pending`
  line `before such a Court shall not be published in any manner.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who contravenes any decision or direction issued under sub-section (3) shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (7650)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Sanction for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7650&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution, suit or other legal proceedings shall be instituted in`
  line `any court of law, except with the previous sanction of the Central Government, against any member of the`
  line `Agency or any person acting on his behalf in respect of anything done or purported to be done in exercise`
  line `of the powers conferred by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (7651)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Trial by Special Court to have precedence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7651&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The trial under this Act of any offence by a`
  line `Special Court shall be held on day-to- day basis on all working days and have precedence over the trial of`
  line `any other case against the accused in any other court (not being a Special Court) and shall be concluded in`
  line `preference to the trial of such other case and accordingly the trial of such other case shall, if necessary,`
  line `remain in abeyance.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (7652)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to transfer cases to regular courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7652&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where, after taking cognizance of any offence, a`
  line `Special Court is of the opinion that the offence is not triable by it, it shall, notwithstanding that it has no`
  line `jurisdiction to try such offence, transfer the case for the trial of such offence to any court having`
  line `jurisdiction under the Code and the Court to which the case is transferred may proceed with the trial of`
  line `the offence as if it had taken cognizance of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (7653)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7653&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, an appeal shall lie from any`
  line `judgment, sentence or order, not being an interlocutory order, of a Special Court to the High Court both`
  line `on facts and on law.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be heard by a bench of two Judges of the High Court and`
  line `shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within a period of three months from the date of admission of the`
  line appeal.
  line
  line `(3) Except as aforesaid, no appeal or revision shall lie to any court from any judgment, sentence or`
  line `order including an interlocutory order of a Special Court.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3) of section 378 of the Code, an appeal shall`
  line `lie to the High Court against an order of the Special Court granting or refusing bail.`
  line
  line `(5) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `the judgment, sentence or order appealed from:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty days`
  line `if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the period of`
  line `thirty days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal shall be entertained after the expiry of period of ninety days.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (7654)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of State Government to designate Court of Session as Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7654&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `22. Power of State Government to ^1[designate Court of Session as] Special Courts.-- (1) The`
  line `State Government may ^2[designate one or more Courts of Session as] Special Courts for the trial of`
  line `offences under any or all the enactments specified in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to the Special Courts ^3[designated] by the State`
  line `Government under sub-section (1) and shall have effect subject to the following modifications, namely--`
  line
  line `(i) references to "Central Government" in sections 11 and 15 shall be construed as references to`
  line `State Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) reference to "Agency" in sub-section (1) of section 13 shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `“investigation agency of the State Government";`
  line
  line `(iii) reference to “Attorney-General for India” in sub-section (3) of section 13 shall be construed`
  line `as reference to "Advocate-General of the State".`
  line
  line `(3) The jurisdiction conferred by this Act on a Special Court shall, until a Special Court is`
  line `^3[designated] by the State Government under sub-section (1) in the case of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, be exercised by the Court of Session of the`
  line `division in which such offence has been committed and it shall have all the powers and follow the`
  line `procedure provided under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(4) On and from the date when the Special Court is ^3[designated] by the State Government the trial of`
  line `any offence investigated by the State Government under the provisions of this Act, which would have`
  line `been required to be held before the Special Court, shall stand transferred to that Court on the date on`
  line `which it is ^3[designated].`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 2019, s. 7, for "constitute" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "constitute one or more" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "constituted" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (7655)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of High Courts to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7655&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make such rules, as it may deem necessary for carrying out the provisions of this Act relating to`
  line `Special Courts within its territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (7656)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7656&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made, under this section after the expiration of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line `25. Power to make`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (7657)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7657&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality to the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of constitution of the Agency and the conditions of service of persons employed in`
  line `the Agency under section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (7658)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916&sectionId=7658&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_00020_200834_1517807326916
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if,`
  line `before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agrees in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not`
  line `be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
